The article discusses the achievements of the U.S.-Japan Nuclear Security Working Group in nine areas. These achievements include cooperation in strengthening nuclear non-proliferation and nuclear security capacity, research and development of nuclear forensics technologies, cooperation on safeguards implementation, sharing best practices for nuclear security in new facility design, cooperation on transport security, converting reactors to reduce the use of highly enriched uranium, implementing nuclear security recommendations, integrating response forces to deal with theft and sabotage, and conducting a joint study on the management of highly enriched uranium and plutonium.